The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 October is 5,159 (597.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 October, there were 566 new confirmed cases (65.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 October, there were 400 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 42% ( 166 extra cases).
